26/08/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The foreign ministry announced on Thursday (25 August) that it will be stepping up diplomatic activities -- in co-ordination with Cyprus -- in relation to Turkey's EU bid and next week's meeting in Brussels of the EU Permanent Representatives Committee. 
Participants will focus on Ankara's implementation of EU conditions, ahead of the start of official membership negotiations on 3 October. 
(ANA - 25/08/05)
